    <etym xml:lang="ru">Происхождение не ясно. Допуская закономерную метатезу %ikʼævda%i ←
        %i*kʼadva%i, можно думать о незасвидетельствованном <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>*kʼad-va</w><gloss><q>течь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><w/><gloss><q>поток</q></gloss></mentioned>, , которое восстанавливается
        на основании <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
            ><lang/><w>k’adi</w><gloss><q>текущий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><w>na-k'adi</w><gloss><q>поток</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>ручей</q></gloss></mentioned>, и др. См. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_kʼada"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The origin is not clear. Supposing the regular metathesis %ikʼævda%i ←
        %i*kʼadva%i, one may think about unattested <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                    ><lang/><w>*kʼad-va</w><gloss><q>leak</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><w/><gloss><q>stream</q></gloss></mentioned>, , which is reconstructed on
        the base of <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
            ><lang/><w>k’adi</w><gloss><q>flowing</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><w>na-k'adi</w><gloss><q>stream</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>brook</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. See <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_kʼada"/>.</etym>
